            "text": " ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "(Rising) —",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " The Daily Poster’s David Sirota joined ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Hill",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "’s Rising morning show to discuss our recent reporting on the relationship between private equity firms and public pensions.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A Message From The Daily Poster:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "One of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Daily Poster",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "’s stories this week perfectly illustrated exactly why independent media’s audiences are growing, and why corporate media’s audience is shrinking.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As you probably saw, we ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "broke open the story",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/biden-boosted-a-pipeline-now-his-aide-could-reap-a-windfall/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " of President Biden’s top domestic policy adviser Susan Rice being in a position to profit off the Biden administration’s backing of a controversial oil pipeline during the climate crisis. This is a hugely important story for obvious reasons.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And yet, for days, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Daily Poster",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " was the only outlet to even mention it.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In so many ways, corporate media is broken — and one of its biggest problems is its partisan lens. So many corporate news outlets judge newsworthiness through a red-versus-blue prism — no matter how legitimately important a story might be, it might be ignored by a corporate media outlet if it doesn’t serve the narrative that the outlet’s particular partisan audience wants.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "html": "<table align=\"center\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><div>\n  <!--[if mso]>\n  <v:rect xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\" xmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\" href=\"https://dailyposter.outpost.pub/public/donate/60818189ad12f332071054b8#/donate\" style=\"height:50px;v-text-anchor:middle;width:140px;\" stroke=\"f\" fillcolor=\"#156CEB\">\n    <w:anchorlock/>\n    <center>\n  <![endif]-->\n      <a href=\"https://dailyposter.outpost.pub/public/donate/60818189ad12f332071054b8#/donate\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color:#2a89b9;color:#ffffff;display:block;font-family:Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:50px;height:50px;text-align:center;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:none;width:140px;border-radius:5px;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;\">Tip Jar &rarr;</a>\n  <!--[if mso]>\n    </center>\n  </v:rect>\n<![endif]-->\n</div></td></tr></table>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Rice story was a perfect example: Had this been a story about Trump and his top aide, it would have been endlessly promoted by outlets like MSNBC and ignored by outlets like Fox News. Instead, our story was erased by Democratic-aligned media outlets, and ultimately only spotlighted by some right-leaning outlets (and now, finally, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "ABC News",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/white-house-adviser-susan-rice-divests-company-building/story?id=78891705",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ").",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In corporate media — and in our larger civic culture — journalism is increasingly just seen as cannon fodder. Decisions about what to promote and ignore are increasingly based on how much media influencers believe a piece of information can be weaponized for their own partisan goals.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And it’s not just news outlets, either — it’s increasingly the same dynamic among the audience itself. You see this on social media all the time — a story about Biden corruption will get retweets and likes among Republican audiences and slammed by Democratic audiences, and then a similar story of Trump corruption will get retweets and likes among Democratic audiences and slammed by Republican audiences.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "At ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Daily Poster",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", we refuse to succumb to this paradigm. We follow the money and hold power accountable, and we don’t care which party that enrages. And we know that doing this is a huge risk — we are betting that in this partisan miasma, there remains an audience that wants real journalism, even if it surfaces truths that are inconvenient to the politicians that the audience may like.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Our big growth in our first year suggests that our bet is correct. We have found thousands of subscribers who want real journalism — and we are working as hard as we can to expand our operations.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Please know that we cannot do this without you. But also know that your support is helping us build a whole new model for independent media. Thank you for being part of the team. Onward.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Rock the boat,",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Sirota",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Photo credit: AP/Susan Walsh",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
